                <h1>Focus on Your Subject: Why Background Matters Less</h1>
                <p>In photography, the main subject should always take center stage. While a backdrop can enhance a shot, it often distracts if it draws too much attention. Focusing on the subject ensures that the viewer's eye is guided to what truly matters, creating a powerful image that resonates. Less is more; prioritize the subject!</p>
